  [Text] According to the deputy minister of economic and 
financial affairs, 40 percent of the nation's tax revenues is 
used for development projects. 
  Speaking Sunday in Mashhad, Daryush Iranbandi added that the 
project to use tax revenues in the provinces for regional 
projects is being studied. 
  At a get-acquainted meeting with the new Khorasan general 
manager of economic and financial affairs, he said: The 
government's policy is that oil revenues should be invested in 
infrastructure affairs and on national projects. 
  He explained: To provide means to investors, henceforth 
investors in regional projects will be exempt from taxes for 
five years. 
  Iranbandi said: With the expansion of tax sources and a view 
to society's economy, an office for deputy governor-general of 
economic affairs will also be created in the provincial general 
offices of economic and financial affairs. 
  He cited the hiring of 1,500 new personnel in the tax 
auditing department as another program in the Ministry of 
Economic and Financial Affairs. 
  At this meeting 'Ali Zarif-Golzar was introduced as the new 
Khorasan general manager of economic and financial affairs. 

