<H3> <TI>   Gonaveh Port Exports 564 Tons of Goods </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gonaveh Port Exports 564 Tons of Goods </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94LA0178E Tehran JAHAN-E ESLAM in Persian 10 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0178E </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran JAHAN-E ESLAM </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] A total of 564 tons of nonoil export goods valued at 
736,929,000 rials [R] went through Gonaveh customs bound for the 
Arab nations of the Persian Gulf during the month of Farvardin 
[21 March-20 April 1994]. 
  The chief of Gonaveh Customs said: This amount represents a 
37-percent increase in terms of weight over the same period last 
year and a decrease of about 9 percent compared to the same 
period last year in terms of value. 
  Zabihollah Jamali added: Likewise, during this period 93 
tons 
of goods valued at R116,442,000 was imported into the country 
through this customs office by various trade and peddler 
cooperatives. 
  He said the main items exported through this customs office 
were plastic and melamine containers and ceramics and that tea, 
automobile tires, and sewing thread were the main import items. 


</TEXT>

