<H3> <TI>   Kohkiluyeh Natural Resources Threatened </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohkiluyeh Natural Resources Threatened </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94LA0178F Tehran JAHAN-E ESLAM in Persian 4 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0178F </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran JAHAN-E ESLAM </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] The director of the Gachsaran Reconstruction Jihad 
said: Natural resources are endangered in the province of 
Kohkiluyeh va Boyer Ahmad due to utilization without regard to 
technical and scientific principles. 
  Engineer Nehavandi said: The amount of livestock in this 
province exceeds the capacity of the pastures and the fuel for 
70 percent of the rural people is procured from the wood of 
forest trees. 
  He added: In addition to this, the conversion of pastures 
for 
low-yield dry farming and improper plowing on slopes has 
destroyed the plant cover and the good fodder. With the 
destruction of the pastures and forests, the soil in this 
province is eroding rapidly. 
  Among the damaging effects of the destruction of natural 
resources in this province, he cited the harmful floods of the 
last few years in Kohkiluyeh va Boyer Ahmad and the excessive 
rural emigration to the cities. 
  Of the 16,000 square kilometers of total area in the 
province 
of Kohkiluyeh va Boyer Ahmad, 230,000 hectares is agricultural 
lands and the rest is forest and pasture. 


</TEXT>

