<F P=103> 94LA0178G </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran JAHAN-E ESLAM </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Petroleum products and flammable materials in the 
Siyahrud River in Qa'emshahr caused a fire on this river Friday. 
  Mohammad 'Ali Lotfi, a fire-fighting official in Qa'emshahr, 
said: The petroleum products came into this river via the sewage 
channels from Textile Factory No. 1. 
  He added: The fire started when someone passing by threw his 
cigarette flame into the river. 
  Lotfi said: The fire immediately covered a large part of the 
river with 20-meter flames. 
  He added: The fire was put out by fire-fighting officials, 
and the petroleum products were also cleaned out of the river. 


