<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Events Service -- Police agents of the East Tehran 
region engaging in the antinarcotics campaign and the campaign 
against narcotics dealers seized 5.5 kg of opium at the home of 
a smuggler along with a large quantity of cans of beer. 
  The Greater Tehran Police Precinct Public Relations Office 
reports: Following the receipt of a report that someone named 
Mehdi was procuring and distributing narcotics at his home on 
Sablan Street in North Tehran, East Tehran Police District 
Agents immediately began an investigation to confirm the truth 
of the report and realized that the aforementioned individual 
was engaged in extensive narcotics procurement and distribution 
activity in the area. The agents obtained a court order and at a 
suitable opportunity they searched the aforementioned party's 
home. While arresting him, they seized 5.5 kg of pure opium, 32 
grams [g] of burnt opium residue, 11 gs of hashish, and 346 cans 
of beer. 
  In this regard the defendant was turned over to the judicial 
authorities along with his file. 


</TEXT>

