<H3> <TI>   Underground Nuclear Test Conducted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Underground Nuclear Test Conducted </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Australia Protests </H4>

<F P=102> BK1606145294 Hong Kong AFP in English 0427 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1606145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sydney, June 16 (AFP) -- The Australian government 
has summoned Chinese Ambassador Hua Junduo [name and title as 
received] to protest his country's June 10 nuclear test blast, 
officials said Thursday. 
  "Senior department officials protested to him about the test 
yesterday (Wednesday) and reiterated our view that it was deeply 
disappointing," said a spokesman for the Department of Foreign 
Affairs and Trade in Canberra. 
  China carried out the underground blast, which had a 
strength 
of 10 to 40 kilotonnes of TNT according Australian scientists, 
at its Lobnor test site on Friday. 

</TEXT>

