<H3> <TI>   COB Leader Asserts Growers Will Not `Move a Finger' for Coca </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    COB Leader Asserts Growers Will Not `Move a Finger' for Coca </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Substitution 

<F P=102>   PY2705141794 La Paz Radio Fides Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2705141794 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Radio Fides Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Coca growers have decided to suspend the 
mobilizations scheduled for this week to protest the 
militarization of coca plantations. 
  Guido Tarqui, leader of the COB [Bolivian Labor Federation] 
Commission for Coca Affairs, has stated that despite the 
militarization of the coca production zones, the coca growers 
are not going to move a finger to make substitutions for or 
reduce their coca plantations. [begin recording] 
  Tarqui: Three important points have been taken 
into account. One of them is that the measures in the 
Cochabamba tropical region, such as the blocking of highways, 
must be implemented because they are in a state of emergency. 
But they have decided that this state of emergency will prevail 
until the end of the COB congress, during which we are going to 
propose declaring a state of emergency in all coca production 
zones. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

