<H3> <TI>   President Denies Plans To Lift Bank Secrecy, Militarize Drug </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Denies Plans To Lift Bank Secrecy, Militarize Drug </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Battle 

<F P=102>   PY2705142894 La Paz Radio Fides Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2705142894 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Radio Fides Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

  [Text] In referring to bank secrecy and the tapping of 
telephone conversations, President Gonzalo Sanchez de Lozada 
stated in Sucre: 
  Nobody is thinking about lifting the bank secrecy. There is 
no plan to this end, and still less to (violate) the specific 
rights of Bolivian people living in democracy. An authorization 
issued by a prosecutor or a judge is necessary to do this. 
  Speaking about the militarization of the Chapare zone, the 
president said: 
  There is no intention of militarizing the struggle against 
drug trafficking. I was never in favor of that when I was a 
member of the opposition, and still less so now that I am in 
government. 

</TEXT>

