<H3> <TI>   Federal Police Commander Found Murdered in Car </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federal Police Commander Found Murdered in Car </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2705034894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0311 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2705034894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 26 May (EFE) -- A source at the Mexico 
City Attorney General's Office told EFE today that Jose Luis 
Fortuna, commander of the Judicial Federal Police, was murdered 
by a gunshot in his forehead and left in his own car on the 
highway to Ajusco on the outskirts of Mexico City. The source 
said Metropolitan Police members found the commander's body in 
the car at approximately 1330 local (1730 GMT) on the border 
between Mexico City and the State of Mexico. 
  The body, the head of which was covered with a sack, 
received 
a gunshot wound to the forehead. A spent 9-mm cartridge was 
found on the car's floor, the official reported. The commander 
was identified by his electoral voting card, which has a 
picture, and the badge of the Attorney General's Office, which 
identified him as commander. 

</TEXT>

