<H3> <TI>   Over One Ton of Marijuana Seized From Truck in Michoacan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Over One Ton of Marijuana Seized From Truck in Michoacan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94WB0039F Mexico City EXCELSIOR in Spanish 7 May 94 p 1-A-3 </F>
<F P=103> 94WB0039F </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City EXCELSIOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Morelia, Michoacan, 6 May--The Attorney General's 
Office [PGR] revealed today that Federal Judicial Police agents 
captured an individual with over a ton of marijuana in his 
possession, on the Los Reyes-Zamora highway. 
  The subject in custody is Enrique Calderon Duran, aged 45, a 
native of Apatzingan, employed as a taxi driver. He claimed to 
have received 500 new pesos for transporting the grass to Los 
Reyes. 
  The driver was carrying 144 packages of the drug, with a 
total weight of 1,012 kg, on a pickup truck, concealed under 
cattle hides intended for tanning. He said that he was supposed 
to deliver the merchandise to someone in Tierra Caliente. 
  The presumed drug trafficker was captured during a routine 
inspection on the aforementioned road, near the municipality of 
Jacona. The agents who discovered the drugs immediately arrested 
the subject, confiscating the packages and the pickup truck. 
  The PGR in Michoacan reported that the drugs and the subject 
in custody were left at the disposal of the Federal Public 
Prosecutor's Office, so that the pertinent interrogations could 
be conducted. 

</TEXT>

