<H3> <TI>   Four Suspected Medellin Cartel Members Detained </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Suspected Medellin Cartel Members Detained </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2305185494 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 0200 GMT 
22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2305185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Arrest warrants have been issued against four 
alleged members of the Medellin Cartel, who were recently 
detained by the National Guard. The arrest warrants were issued 
against four alleged perpetrators of drug trafficking based on 
Article 33 on the Basic Law on Drugs and Psychotropic Substances 
and on Article 83 of the Penal Code. The arrest warrants were 
issued via the 48th Court and the First Criminal District of the 
Caracas Metropolitan Judicial District, which is headquartered 
in Los Cortijo de Lourdes. 
  Reportedly, this particular branch of the Medellin Cartel is 
using this nation as a bridge for drug trafficking to Europe and 
North America. Colonel Jairo Casimiro Coronel Figueroa, 
National Guard director of efforts against drug trafficking, 
identified the detained suspects as Ruben Dario Pelais Munera, 
German Perez Zapata, [name indistinct], and Luis Fernando 
Martinez. Meanwhile, [words indistinct] Carlos San Vincens 
Clavera were released. These last two had been detained for 
questioning. It was also learned that these four individuals 
will remain at the Judicial Detention Center in Las Flores, 
Catia. 

</TEXT>

