<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Roundup for 16-22 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Narcotics Roundup for 16-22 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2305154994 </F>
<F P=103> BK2305154994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on narcotics developments in South Asia, Southeast Asia, 
and the Pacific monitored by Bangkok Bureau between 16 and 22 
May 1994. Source information is given in parentheses after each 
item. 
<H8>  SOUTHEAST ASIA </H8>
<H5>  Burma </H5>
<H5>  Defense Services Members Seize 2.204 Kg of Heroin in Pekon </H5>
  Acting on a tip, members of the Defense Services 
Intelligence 
Unit and the regional battalion searched a house in Nyaunggon 
Ward, Pekon on 8 April. They found two people in the house with 
six packets of Double UO Globe brand heroin weighing 2.204 kg. 
(Rangoon THE NEW LIGHT OF BURMA in English 13 Apr 94 p 7) 
<H5>  Philippines </H5>
<H5>  Narcotics Command Burns Marijuana Plantation </H5>
  A joint team led by agents of Narcotics Command Region 2 
recently burned about 50 million pesos worth of marijuana plants 
on a 50 hectare site on Mount Chumanchil, Butbot village, 
Tinglayan town, Kalinga-Apayao Province. (Manila MANILA 
BULLETIN in English 15 May 94 p AT-2) 
<H5>  Woman Arrested Smuggling Drugs Into Manila Jail </H5>
  A drug organization inside the Manila city jail was broken 
up 
on 14 May when guards arrested Cecilia Nagateja, 34, as she 
tried to smuggle in a large volume of methamphetamine 
hydrochloride hidden in her underwear. The suspect said she had 
been delivering the drug to two inmates for several months. 
(Manila MANILA STANDARD in English 15 May 94 p 7) 
<H5>  Narcotics Command Arrests Suspect With Methamphetamine </H5>
Hydrochloride 
  The Narcotics Command arrested Alfredo Bayot after he sold 
methamphetamine hydrochloride to an undercover agent. Bayot is 
thought to supply methamphetamine hydrochloride to patrons of 
five-star hotels in Manila and Pasay City. Two hundred grams of 
the drug were confiscated from the suspect. (Manila THE MANILA 
CHRONICLE in English 17 May 94 p 6) 
<H5>  Singapore </H5>
<H5>  Narcotics Bureau Seizes Eight Kg of Heroin, Arrests Six </H5>
  The Central Narcotics Bureau dismantled a "major drug 
syndicate" operating in Singapore when its officers arrested six 
people and seized nearly eight kg of heroin on 19 May. The 
suspects, aged between 24 and 42, are believed to have been 
operating since March. (Singapore Singapore Broadcasting 
Corporation in English 1100 GMT 19 May 94) 
<H5>  Thailand </H5>
<H5>  Nigerian Arrested With Heroin; Second Incident Possibly </H5>
Related 
  On 6 May, Nigerian national J.N. Okafor, 23, was arrested 
with 115 tubes of heroin weighing a total of 76 kg. The drugs 
were hidden inside 162 pairs of jeans found on the premises of a 
cargo forwarding company in Pom Prap Sattru Phai District, 
Bangkok. The company's management revealed that the narcotics 
were sent by a Nigerian man identified as Valentino. 
  On 19 May, police found four sacks containing more than 93 
tubes of heroin weighing about 33 kg at the same company. 
Police suspect that the two incidents are connected. (Bangkok 
BANGKOK POST in English 20 May 94 p 2) 

</TEXT>

