<F P=100> NEAR EAST &amp; SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> INDIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bombay Police Destroy Over 5,000 Kg of Drugs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bombay Police Destroy Over 5,000 Kg of Drugs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94WD0369A Bombay THE TIMES OF INDIA in English 22 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0369A </F>
<F P=104>  Bombay THE TIMES OF INDIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Bombay, April 21--The narcotics cell of the city 
police today destroyed 5,278 kg of drugs valued at Rs 425 crores 
in India, and many times this amount in the international 
market, at Reti Bunder, Sewri. 
  The narcotic and psychotropic substances destroyed included 
heroin, mandrax, hashish, opium and ganja. The drugs were 
destroyed after following the special procedure laid down by the 
NDPS [expansion not given] Act. It has to be followed since the 
courts have as yet not delivered judgment in the various cases 
filed by the police. 
  To preserve the evidence, representative samples and 
photographs of the drug seized are taken in the presence of 
metropolitan magistrate. The specially-constituted NDPS courts 
have to be then approached for permission to destroy the drugs. 
  The Act provides for their pre-trial destruction since there 
is always a fear that they might be stolen or substituted. 
Besides, a lot of space has to be provided for storage. 

</TEXT>

