<H3> <TI>   State Laboratory Tests Indicate `Super-Strong' Heroin in </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Laboratory Tests Indicate `Super-Strong' Heroin in </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Circulation 

<F P=102>   NC2405194594 Athens ATHENS NEWS in English 24 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2405194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ATHENS NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Super-strong heroin, up to 55 percent pure, is 
circulating in Greece. 
  Among confiscated samples sent for inspection to the state 
laboratory was the same heroin that killed Vasilis Tsaklof, 
containing 24 percent of the drug and 54 percent of lactose. 
That combination in itself is not necessarily fatal but the 
victim had combined it with Hypnostedon pills. 
  Attica police headquarters said that heroin in the Greek 
market used to be only ten to 15 percent pure. The state lab 
inspected ten different samples of the drug, confiscated in 
Athens, and discovered that their heroin content ranged from 22 
to 55 percent. 
  The number of victims this month in Athens from "instant 
death" heroin has now risen to 15 whilst heroin addict Dhimos 
Tsagalidhis, 27, is in a coma at a hospital in Serres, northern 
Greece. 

</TEXT>

