<H3> <TI>   Opium Production in Tajikistan, Drug Smuggling Through </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opium Production in Tajikistan, Drug Smuggling Through </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Uzbekistan   Increasing 

<F P=102> LD2305195494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1811 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the International Narcotics Control 
Committee, the production of opium in Tajikistan has grown by 
more than 1.5 times to reach 650 tons a year since the beginning 
of the war in Afghanistan in December 1979. 
  In addition, well-informed sources in Tashkent told Interfax 
that the quantity of narcotics confiscated during smuggling or 
transit through Uzbekistan in 1992-1993 has increased greatly. 
More than 16 tons of hashish, marijuana, opium and synthetic 
narcotics have been registered in criminal files over this 
period. Since the beginning of this year, ten criminal cases 
have been launched following attempts to smuggle narcotics to 
Uzbekistan. 

</TEXT>

