<F P=101> KYRGYZSTAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN To Provide Assistance for Country's Antidrug Effort </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN To Provide Assistance for Country's Antidrug Effort </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605104394 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 2300 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kyrgyz </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Giorgio Giacomelli, UN deputy secretary-general 
and executive director of the UN fund for drug abuse, visited 
Kyrgyzstan 23-25 May. [passage omitted] 
  Summarizing the results of this visit, Giacomelli emphasized 
that Kyrgyzstan is seriously tackling this issue. The republic 
was the first in the region to establish contacts with the 
United Nations in fighting the spread of drugs. Therefore the 
United Nations is willing to support Kyrgyzstan in addressing 
this issue. 
  The state commission for control over drug trafficking will 
be provided with technical assistance: video films, laboratory 
equipment, and a car, worth a total of $500,000. A special 
program will be adopted which envisions cooperation aimed at 
upgrading legislation related to drug abuse, consultations, 
training of experts, and sharing information. 
  An office of the UN's fund for drug abuse has been set up in 
Tashkent. It will also assist Kyrgyzstan. 

</TEXT>

