<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Increase in EC Tariff Benefits Viewed as Reward for Antidrug </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Increase in EC Tariff Benefits Viewed as Reward for Antidrug </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Efforts 

<F P=102>   PA0506000794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal 
A Network in Spanish 1730 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0506000794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal 
A Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by J. Orlando Gomez; from the "Midday Television </F>
Newscast"] 
  [Text] Despite Colombia's poor image in the realm of human 
rights violations, it is very possible that the EC countries 
will increase its tariff benefits. Because of the huge 
sacrifices Colombia, Bolivia, Ecuador, and Peru have made in 
blood and money in the struggle against drug trafficking, the EC 
four years ago established a system that allows these Latin 
American countries' products to enter the 12 EC countries 
without paying tariffs or taxes. Thanks to this measure, a 
considerable amount of Colombian exports are entering the old 
continent without any problem. EC Ambassador Jose Luis Benito 
Prior discussed the issue. 
  [Begin Benito Prior recording] This measure covers over 90 
percent of Colombia's exports, all industrial products, and a 
long list of farm products. Colombia, therefore, can 
congratulate itself for this positive atmosphere. [end 
recording] 
  Thanks to the good work these countries have done in the 
struggle against drug trafficking, these preferential tariffs 
may be extended for another 10 years. 
  [Begin Benito Prior recording] In Europe we appreciate all 
the efforts that Colombia and other Latin American countries are 
making in this struggle. Much must still be done, and together 
we must try to foster a spirit of cooperation. [end recording] 
  These favorable conditions and terms will allow Colombia's 
most competitive products to establish roots on the old 
continent within a few years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

