<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> CHILE </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Most-Wanted' Chilean Drug Trafficker Recaptured </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Most-Wanted' Chilean Drug Trafficker Recaptured </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0106152694 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0149 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0106152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santiago, 31 May (EFE) -- Selim Valenzuela, the 
most-wanted Chilean drug trafficker, was recaptured today after 
he escaped on 28 May while being transported to prison from a 
hospital. 
  The Chilean Government's television channel reported today 
that Valenzuela was arrested again by police near Valparaiso, 
the country's main port. Valparaiso is 125 km northwest of 
Santiago. 
  The criminal paid $5,000 to the prison guards taking him 
back 
to prison after he underwent a medical checkup at a Valparaiso 
hospital. 
  Valenzuela, who was detained on 11 March, allegedly has been 
involved in a shipment of 40 kg of cocaine to Sweden in 1992, a 
case in which two other Chileans have been sentenced to a 
10-year prison term in Stockholm. 

</TEXT>

